menu_builditem
[TITLE]The Manual: View Building Items[/TITLE]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]How to Get Here[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_BUILDITEM] from the main view.
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Description[C:7:0:0]
[B]
This menu allows you to look inside buildings.  A cursor will appear on the screen.  Use [IKEY:CURSOR_UP][IKEY:CURSOR_DOWN][IKEY:CURSOR_LEFT][IKEY:CURSOR_RIGHT][IKEY:CURSOR_UPLEFT][IKEY:CURSOR_UPRIGHT][IKEY:CURSOR_DOWNLEFT][IKEY:CURSOR_DOWNRIGHT] to move the cursor.
[B]
The contents of the closest building are displayed, along with instructions on how to select items.  You can view items from this menu, and you can
order the removal of the building.  You can also view the progress of building construction from this menu.
[B]
Depending on the building, some special symbols can appear to give you more information.
[C:3:0:1]TSK[C:7:0:0] A task is associated to this object.[R]
[C:7:0:1][[B]][C:7:0:0] The object is part of the building.[R]
[C:6:0:1][[T]][C:7:0:0] The object is a trade good.[R]
[C:2:0:1][[A]][C:7:0:0] This is an animal caught in a trap.[R]
[C:6:0:0][[B]][C:7:0:0] This object is bait in a trap.[R]
[C:5:0:1][[L]][C:7:0:0] This object is loaded in a siege engine.[R]
[C:0:0:1][[B]][C:7:0:0] The object is enclosed in a coffin.[R]
[C:1:0:1][[B]][C:7:0:0] The object is associated to the building in another way.[R]
[B]
If the building is cluttered, that information will be displayed at the top right of the menu.
[B]
[LINK:data/help/building_clutter]Building Clutter[/LINK]
